OL,3,CMan who stabbed victim's skull in
OL,4,Cunprovoked nightclub attack jailed
OL,6,F"As well as permanent scarring, Mr
OL,7,FThompson will never be able to fully
OL,8,Frecover to lead a full and active life
OL,9,Fas a result of this vicious assault.
OL,11,F"I am grateful to the jury for their
OL,12,Fcareful consideration of the evidence
OL,13,Fin delivering their verdict. It was
OL,14,Fvery clear it was his intention to
OL,15,Fkill Mr Thompson, and he will now face
OL,16,Fthe consequences with a lengthy prison
OL,17,Fsentence, which is fully justified for
OL,18,Fthe ferocity of the attack.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
